metadata.name: De/FragV2 #319
metadata.description:
The second piece in this series is dedicated to another fundamental algorithm in computer graphics: Voronoi. It's origin precedes its use with computers by several decades, or centuries, depending on who to credit, since science always is a continuum. In the generative art & design field, the algorithm has been an instrumental tool for generation(s) of practioners, sadly often to the point of turning clich√©.

In this piece I've attempted to "break" the classic resulting aesthetics of this algorithm and focus more on revealing its inner workings. There are many ways of computing a Voronoi diagram. The so called Jump Flood Algorithm (JFA) proved to be the visually most interesting approach to me. Again, as with the previous De/Frag piece, here the algorithm has been slowed down, timesliced and customized in dozens of ways to result in a more painterly character overall and produce a variety of new shapes & textures.

Fullscreen compatible (Press 'S' to toggle square frame). Made with love & thi.ng/umbrella

metadata.name: Alles #60
metadata.description:
Alles is a companion to St√∂rungen. It builds upon the principles - both aesthetic and programatic, that were laid down in that piece and they are intended to be enjoyed together

This piece is created in p5js, but is also intended to be plotted. Plotting will not allow for the blurring or color in the piece, but will instead give you a single color version that you can print.

Open the token in a new window and:
- add &highres=true to the URL to get a highres image for printing
- add &svg=true to have the program create a plottable SVG
- double-click to download a PNG or SVG

metadata.name: St√∂rungen #174
metadata.description:
St√∂rungen is an exercise in suprematism in generative art. Not a new concept by any means, but (hopefully) uniquely applied.

In this work a single line is drawn from the center of the artwork, spiraling out and being perturbed by various constraints and disturbed by various controlling forces. These perturbations produce different illusions and, when combined, create feeling.

This piece is created in p5js, but is also intended to be plotted. Plotting will not allow for the blurring or color in the piece, but will instead give you a single color version of the perturbed spiral that you can print.

Open the token in a new window and:
- add &highres=true to the URL to get a highres image for printing
- add &svg=true to have the program create a plottable SVG
- double-click to download a PNG or SVG

metadata.name: Faltantrieb #26
metadata.description:
A simple particle system, folded, convolved, distorted and decorated into something wild and beautiful.

Made with p5js.

Double click to download
Add ?highres=true to the URL to get a higher resolution output (be aware that this will require a powerful computer)

Please note that this token has been optimized for Chrome. It will work in firefox but is much slower at generating an output and uses fewer particles.

metadata.name: Font Frenzy #11
metadata.description: Exuberant and lively piece of art crafted utilizing the ASCII art technique. This creation amalgamates an assortment of fonts and typefaces, resulting in a tumultuous, seemingly disorderly impact. The elaborate and multifaceted characteristics of the ASCII art form are accentuated in this work, where each singular character adds to the complete structure. "Typeface Turmoil" was brought to life with the aid of ChatGPT, an extensive language model developed by OpenAI, offering imaginative guidance and motivation.

metadata.name: zancannabis #136
metadata.description:
zancannabis is a celebration of 4/20 2023 and is of course a respectful parody of the artwork from the legend that is zancan.
this artwork uses code to randomly place illustrations of cannabis plants created using midjourney ai with post-production in Illustrator and Photoshop.

The work is in no way related to the artist zancan and is not intended to fool anyone into thinking so thus does not affect the original artists market or value.
